 Yuguda Hassan Kila, a member representing Gwaram Federal Constituency of Jigawa State has died. He died at 65. According to reports, the Chairman of the House Committee on Customs died on Thursday afternoon, March 4 at the National Hospital, Abuja after battling with an ailment. In 2015, he was appointed member of the House of Representatives on the platform of the ruling APC to represent Gwaram Constituency, he won the same position in 2019 as well. Reacting to his demise, Governor Baduru of Jigawa State expressed sadness while sending condolences to the family of the deceased and the state as a whole.